      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "China's expansive claims in the South China Sea are widely contested and are not uniformly recognized by international law. While China bases its claims largely on historical rights, these claims frequently conflict with the rulings of international bodies like the Permanent Court of Arbitration. Many nations and legal experts view these claims as overreaching and inconsistent with established principles of freedom of navigation. Therefore, the claims are actively being challenged and are not accepted as definitive under current international maritime law.",
      "source": "target",
